# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your .python-version of the development
#   environment. For an app, you check it in.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if development is done on different OSes, lock failures may occur.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be submitted unless it's a library.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be submitted unless it's a library.
# .pdm.toml
# .pdm-python
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/lincolnloop/layman and pdm
